  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2.32.0-stable-021891a3`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nReturns transaction receipt or descriptive error\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nReturns error\r\n``` method=eth_getTransactionReceipt reqid=43 t=490.774Âµs err=\"getReceipts error: nonce too low: address 0x0A5FdF471c340eF9DD0d6fC86Fc61981220Da2f6, tx: 5936 state: 37425\"```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n`erigon --prune=cht --prune.r.before=11052984`\r\n`getTransactionReceipt('0x95cb4188ff8a3e183beca6ea9dd93eb01ad429b8d2c1b5340a267ed8f5836e70')` (any transaction before prune block)\r\n\r\nThe address in the error is the sender of the first transaction in the block of the target transaction, my understanding is it attempts to apply all the transactions in the block but it seems to be starting with oldest indexed state instead of previous block.\r\n\r\nI'm guessing this isn't supposed to work, but the error is pretty confusing, perhaps somewhere in `ComputeTxEnv` should return an error if trying to load a pruned block?",
